OL,3,CAndrew RT Davies' exit signals start
OL,4,Cof ideological battle for Welsh Tories
OL,6,F"It was important that people couldn't
OL,7,Fdo their crimes in the dark - they
OL,8,Fwere going to be seen," said one
OL,9,Fsupporter.
OL,11,FThe result: nine votes to keep him,
OL,12,Fseven to get rid of him. He won the
OL,13,Fvote, but at what cost?
OL,15,F"He wasn't angry," said one source.
OL,16,F"He's a happy warrior."
OL,18,FDespite the victory, the group
OL,19,Fremained deeply divided, leaving him
OL,20,Fwith no choice but to step aside.
