OL,3,CAndrew RT Davies' exit signals start
OL,4,Cof ideological battle for Welsh Tories
OL,6,FSupporters of Andrew RT Davies believe
OL,7,Fhis strategy was the right one:
OL,8,Freaching out to working-class voters
OL,9,Fwho have historically not supported
OL,10,Fthe Conservatives but might back
OL,11,FReform UK. Critics argue that pursuing
OL,12,Fa Reform-esque approach is futile,
OL,13,Finsisting the party must appeal to the
OL,14,Fcentre ground instead.
OL,16,FThis internal conflict is likely to
OL,17,Fplay out in any upcoming leadership
OL,18,Felection. The choice: stick with the
OL,19,Fcurrent strategy but under a new
OL,20,Fleader, or change direction entirely.
